        <p>Every "listing management tool" falls in one of four buckets. Pick by the bucket that fits your location count, not the homepage pitch:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Budget distributors</strong> — Moz Local, Synup. Cover the directories that matter most at a per-location price under $20/mo.</li>
          <li><strong>Mid-market platforms</strong> — BrightLocal, Semrush, SE Ranking. Listings plus rank tracking and reports in one suite.</li>
          <li><strong>Enterprise sync</strong> — Yext, Uberall. Real-time push to the largest publisher network, built for 25+ locations.</li>
          <li><strong>Done-for-you services</strong> — theStacc, Whitespark. Humans handle the listing work alongside content and citations.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">The per-location pricing trap</div>
          <p>Yext, Birdeye, and Uberall price per location. At 2 locations it feels reasonable. At 25 locations it is <strong>$5,000+/mo before reports.</strong> Always run the math at your actual location count before signing the annual contract.</p>
